title: Max Ernst - a Retrospective (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Guggenheim Museum | 1975 | Pdf | Eng | 271 pag | 16.1 MB

My wanderings, my unrest, my impatience, my doubts, my beliefs, my hallucinations,
my loves, my outbursts of anger, my revolts, my contradictions,
my refusals to submit to any discipline . . . have not created a climate favorable
to the creation of a peaceful, serene work. My work is like my conduct;
not harmonious in the sense of the classical composers, or even in the sense of
the classical revolutionaries. Rebellious, heterogeneous, full of contradiction,
it is unacceptable to specialists of art, culture, conduct, logic, morality. But it
does have the ability to enchant my accomplices: poets, pataphysicians and a
few illiterates
